===Noun===
'''[[one]]-[[night]] [[stand]]'''

# An occasion when a performer or team of them (especially in [[vaudeville]]) expects to perform at a theater for a single evening.
#{{idiom}} A single [[sexual]] [[encounter]] between individuals, where at least one of the parties has no immediate [[intention]] or [[expectation]] of establishing a longer-[[term]] sexual or [[romantic]] [[relationship]]. As the phrase implies, the relationship lasts for only one night.

